-- Chrysler U.S. August sales slide 34 percent
-- 
-- Wed Sep 3, 2008 3:43pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/03/us-usa-autosales-chrysler-idUSN0342344020080903

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Chrysler LLC said on Wednesday that U.S. auto sales fell 34 percent in August. 

 The automaker's U.S. sales fell to 110,235 vehicles in August, from 168,203 vehicles a year earlier. The company said it had 380,560 units of inventory, or a 93-day supply at the end of August, down 15 percent compared with August 2007. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta ; editing by Carol Bishopric)